                        <physDesc>
                            <objectDesc>
                                <supportDesc material="parchment">
                                    <support>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="1r" to="152v" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <material>Parchment</material>
                                            <dimensions type="leaf">
                                                <height quantity="295" unit="mm"/>
                                                <width quantity="230" unit="mm"/>
                                            </dimensions>
                                        </p>
                                    </support>
                                    <extent>
                                        <measure type="textblockLeaves" quantity="152" unit="folios"/>
                                    </extent>
                                    <foliation>Paragraphs indicated by Roman numerals in the margin. </foliation>
                                    <condition>Holes in the parchment, but no loss of text. <locus from="14v" to="14v" scheme="folios"/>: text damaged by liquid spill, which also appears on other leaves. Several leaves have been damaged by cuts, e.g. on <locus from="20" to="20" scheme="folios"/> where a horizontal cut has been made below the text, or on <locus from="27" to="27" scheme="folios"/> where a strip of parchment has been cut from the bottom of the page. Between <locus from="68" to="68" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="69" to="69" scheme="folios"/> a stub of a bifolium is visible, but there is no interruption of the text. The book block is partially cracked, e.g. between <locus from="69" to="69" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="70" to="70" scheme="folios"/>.</condition>
                                </supportDesc>
                                <layoutDesc>
                                    <layout columns="1" writtenLines="33">
                                        <locus from="6r" to="152r" scheme="folios"/>
                                        <dimensions type="written">
                                            <height quantity="235" unit="mm"/>
                                            <width quantity="170" unit="mm"/>
                                        </dimensions>
                                        <note>Pricking in the margin. Blind ruling.</note>
                                    </layout>
                                </layoutDesc>
                            </objectDesc>
                            <handDesc>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-1">Carolingian minuscule. </handNote>
                            </handDesc>
                            <additions>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Top of page, in dark ink: <quote>B. 28.</quote> Spread over the upper part of page, in dark ink by a medieval hand: various exerpts, perhaps pen-trials, e.g. Matt 12:43 repeated several times, part of psalm 118:28 and others. Centre page, in dark ink by medieval hand:<quote xml:lang="la"> hic est liber beati dyonisii pro in cr-s digne cruciatur diues in igne / Vlceribus plenum quia non satiauit egenum </quote>. Right margin in brown ink: drawing of knot-like shape. Bottom of page, in faded ink by later medieval hand: <quote>vi vii:xx xvii</quote>; below, in dark ink by later hand: <quote xml:lang="la">Rabanus Maurus in Libros regum.</quote>
                                    </note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="6r" to="6r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Lower margin in dark ink: two symbols that look like a C and a cross. According to <bibl>
                                            <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107187">Lehmann (1934)</title>
                                            <citedRange from="168" to="168" unit="page"/>
                                        </bibl>, this is typical for the abbey of Saint-Denis.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="6r" to="152v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Scattered glosses by a contemporary hand, usually in the form of a single word. In the margins, references by a contemporary hand to authoritites/sources by use of 1-2 letters (e.g. B for Bede). References to Migne in pencil by a modern hand.</note>
                                </p>
                            </additions>
                            <decoDesc>
                                <p>Main text in blackish brown ink, rubrics in red.</p>
                                <decoNote type="initials">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="6r" to="6r" scheme="folios"/>: plain chapter initial F with interior reserved shapes over 5 lines in black. <locus from="40r" to="40r" scheme="folios"/>: plain chapter initial F over 5 lines in black. <locus from="70r" to="70r" scheme="folios"/>: plain chapter initial E over 2 lines (+ extending above the line) in black. <locus from="121v" to="121v" scheme="folios"/>: penwork chapter initial P over 6 lines in black. <locus from="1v" to="150v" scheme="folios"/>: plain initials over 1-2 lines (+ extending above or below the line) in black or red. On <locus from="82v" to="83r" scheme="folios"/> the initials are touched in red.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote type="images">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="152r" to="152r" scheme="folios"/>: ink drawing of two male figures. One larger (ca 10 cm) of a standing man in full figure seen from the front portrayed with fairly elaborate clothing and a crown or hat; the other small (ca 4 cm) of a bearded man in half figure profile.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote type="images">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="152v" to="152v" scheme="folios"/>: full-page drawing of a circular labyrinth-like shape. At the bottom some faint vegetative ornaments and small sitting man with a triangular hat (possibly later additions).</p>
                                </decoNote>
                            </decoDesc>
